The paper deals with the vertex coloring problem, which is a well-known problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem also has many applications in operations research (cs.OR) and scheduling, which are both related to optimization and algorithms. The paper proposes a heuristic algorithm for solving the problem, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm also involves generating initial solutions, which can be seen as a data structure problem (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents experimental results and performance analysis, which can be considered as a machine learning task (cs.LG).
